# Frontend Patterns

- `src/App.jsx` owns top-level routes.
- Use existing layouts: `PublicLayout`, `TradingLayout`, `WorkbenchLayout`, and `PicksLayout`.
- Put investor/tooling app work under `src/trading`.
- Put public explanation pages under `src/marketing`.
- Put weekly picks work under `src/picks`.
- Put blog work under `src/blog`.
- Put shared shell, nav, SEO, and auth code under `src/shared`.
- Keep static workbench pages browser-runnable and compatible with copy into `dist/workbench`.
- Do not hardcode Firebase web config. Use `import.meta.env.VITE_FIREBASE_*`.
- Avoid guaranteed-profit or risk-free language in options content.

Run `npm run build` after frontend route, asset, Firebase config, or Vite changes.
